JOHANNESBURG – A video of a Honda Fit driver trying to overtake a large, slow-moving truck is making rounds on social media. The video ends bitterly with the Honda flying through the trees and into the bushes. It begins with the Honda driver attempting to overtake the truck on a narrow road before losing control, colliding with the side of the truck and flying off the road. READ: Authorities concerned about road fatalities It was shared on Facebook by a user Kyle 'Link' Suttie, and has been viewed more than 30,000 times. According to reports, the incident took place on the Beitbridge Road in Zimbabwe, near the South African border while the vehicles were en route to Harare. Luckily, only minor injuries were reported from the incident. eNCA